sequenceDiagram
    participant "Frontend SPA" as FrontendSPA
    participant "Backend API" as BackendAPI
    participant "PostgreSQL Database" as PostgreSQLDatabase
    participant "AWS S3 Storage" as AWSS3Storage
    participant "RabbitMQ Broker" as RabbitMQBroker

    activate BackendAPI
    FrontendSPA->>BackendAPI: 1. POST /api/v1/projects/from-sow (multipart/form-data)
    BackendAPI-->>FrontendSPA: 201 Created - { projectId, sowDocumentId }
    BackendAPI->>BackendAPI: 2. Validate request: Authorize role, validate file type/size, confirm active Client exists.
    BackendAPI-->>BackendAPI: Validation success or throws exception.
    BackendAPI->>PostgreSQLDatabase: 3. BEGIN TRANSACTION
    PostgreSQLDatabase-->>BackendAPI: Transaction started.
    BackendAPI->>PostgreSQLDatabase: 4. INSERT INTO Projects; INSERT INTO SowDocuments; INSERT INTO AuditLogs
    PostgreSQLDatabase-->>BackendAPI: New ProjectId, SowDocumentId, AuditLogId
    BackendAPI->>AWSS3Storage: 5. PutObjectAsync(bucket, key, fileStream)
    AWSS3Storage-->>BackendAPI: HTTP 200 OK
    BackendAPI->>PostgreSQLDatabase: 6. COMMIT TRANSACTION
    PostgreSQLDatabase-->>BackendAPI: Transaction committed.
    BackendAPI->>RabbitMQBroker: 7. Publish('sow_processing_exchange', 'sow.uploaded.v1', eventMessage)
    RabbitMQBroker-->>BackendAPI: Publisher Acknowledgment

    note over BackendAPI: Transactional Boundary: The database operations (steps 4, 5) and the S3 upload (step 6) must be t...
    note over RabbitMQBroker: Reliable Event Dispatch: Publishing the 'SowUploaded' event (step 8) occurs only after the databa...

    deactivate BackendAPI
